  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen you run a failing transaction in the console, it doesn't indicate the transaction hash anywhere, only the VM exception.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nDefine a contract with a Solidity function that does a revert, e.g.:\r\n```solidity\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.24;\r\n\r\ncontract Reverts {\r\n  function fail() public {\r\n    revert(\"test-failure\");\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun `truffle develop` and do:\r\n```\r\ntruffle(develop)> (await Reverts.new()).fail()\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe output in the console should be pretty and have useful information, including:\r\n- REVERT reason string\r\n- transaction hash\r\n- probably other stuff\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: Returned error: VM Exception while processing transaction: revert test-failure\r\n    at XMLHttpRequest._onHttpResponseEnd (/Users/gnidan/src/work/truffle/node_modules/xhr2-cookies/xml-http-request.ts:345:8)\r\n    at XMLHttpRequest._setReadyState (/Users/gnidan/src/work/truffle/node_modules/xhr2-cookies/xml-http-request.ts:219:8)\r\n    at XMLHttpRequestEventTarget.dispatchEvent (/Users/gnidan/src/work/truffle/node_modules/xhr2-cookies/xml-http-request-event-target.ts:44:13)\r\n    at XMLHttpRequest.request.onreadystatechange (/Users/gnidan/src/work/truffle/node_modules/web3-providers-http/src/index.js:79:13)\r\n    at /Users/gnidan/src/work/truffle/packages/truffle-provider/wrapper.js:101:9\r\n    at /Users/gnidan/src/work/truffle/node_modules/web3-core-requestmanager/src/index.js:140:36\r\n    at Object.ErrorResponse (/Users/gnidan/src/work/truffle/node_modules/web3-core-helpers/src/errors.js:29:16)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.0-beta.1\r\n",
